  "response": "Here are some productive and appropriate things to do when bored in an office:\n\n1. Professional activities:\n- Organize files and documents\n- Clean up email inbox\n- Update your resume\n- Learn a new work-related skill online\n- Read industry publications\n- Plan upcoming projects\n- Network with colleagues\n\n2. Skill development:\n- Take online courses\n- Watch professional development videos\n- Learn a new language\n- Practice typing skills\n- Read educational articles\n\n3. Quick mental breaks:\n- Do a crossword or sudoku puzzle\n- Play a quick brain-training game\n- Take a short walk\n- Do some stretching\n- Practice mindfulness or meditation\n\n4. Creative tasks:\n- Brainstorm new ideas for work\n- Write down professional goals\n- Sketch or doodle\n- Plan personal or professional improvements\n\n5. Technology-based activities:\n- Listen to educational podcasts\n- Watch professional webinars\n- Take online skills tests\n- Read professional blogs\n\n6. Light work tasks:\n- Reorganize digital files\n- Update contact lists\n- Review and update work procedures\n- Prepare meeting notes or reports\n\nRemember to balance these activities with your primary work responsibilities and maintain professionalism.",
